OL,3,CSmartphones: Time To Live Without Them?
OL,5,FWe also meet 17 year old Libbi from
OL,6,FBolton who, like many teenage girls,
OL,7,Floves her smartphone. She says her
OL,8,Fphone is the first thing she sees in
OL,9,Fthe morning, and the last thing she
OL,10,Fsees at night, with her screen time
OL,11,Famassing up to 9 hours per day. For
OL,12,Ffour days, Libbi's grandad Alan will
OL,13,Ftake charge of her smartphone whilst
OL,14,FLibbi will be given a so-called
OL,15,F'dumbphone'; a basic handset allowing
OL,16,Fonly phone calls and text messages. We
OL,17,Ffollow their journey to see how they
OL,18,Fget on with the help of Psychologist
OL,19,FMaryhan Munt.
