OL,3,CSmartphones: Time To Live Without Them?
OL,5,FTonight also speaks to Headteacher
OL,6,FDamian McBeath from the John Wallis
OL,7,FAcademy in Ashford, who says banning
OL,8,Fsmartphones has been
OL,9,F"transformational" for their school.
OL,10,FEvery morning, pupils place their
OL,11,Fphones, smartwatches and earpods in a
OL,12,Fmagnetically locking pouch where they
OL,13,Fstay for the rest of the school day.
OL,14,FPupils can only access phone pouches
OL,15,Fat the end of the school day once
OL,16,Fteachers have unlocked the magnets.
